content='The proposed audited validation panel is technically appropriate, but the final instruction says not to repeat previously conducted simulations, and the provided “Simulated Molecules” list already includes essentially all of the validation-panel candidates and their alternate encodings (e.g., benzene, acetonitrile, ethanol, dimethyl ether, formamide, urea, methylurea, carbamoyl fluoride, acetamide, carbon dioxide, carbonyl fluoride).\n\nGiven that constraint, I should not rerun any of those molecules now. Therefore I will not launch simulations, because any compliant run from the requested panel would violate the “do not repeat previously conducted simulations” rule.\n\nBest next action under the constraints:\n- Pause new calculations.\n- Treat the current state as validation-blocked.\n- Request either:\n  1. permission to rerun the audited panel despite prior execution, or\n  2. access to batch/row-level provenance metadata so the identity issue can be diagnosed without repeating molecules.\n\nOnce reruns are authorized, the correct execution would be:\n- several parallel duplicate/alternate-SMILES jobs,\n- isolated single-entry jobs,\n- and independently reordered mixed batches,\nfor only the small audited panel.\nI can’t run the requested validation panel as-is, because every key panel molecule appears in the “Simulated Molecules” list, and you explicitly said not to repeat previously conducted simulations.\n\nSo the correct action is:\n- run no new simulations now,\n- keep the workflow in validation-blocked/quarantine mode,\n- request authorization to rerun the audited panel despite the no-repeat rule.\n\nWhy:\n- The technical plan is sound.\n- But benzene, acetonitrile, ethanol, dimethyl ether, formamide, urea, methylurea, carbamoyl fluoride, acetamide, carbon dioxide, and carbonyl fluoride—and their alternate encodings—have already been simulated.\n- Repeating them would violate your instruction.\n\nRecommended next step:\n1. Override the no-repeat restriction for the minimal validation panel only, or\n2. provide provenance/batch-mapping data so the failure can be diagnosed without reruns.\n\nIf you authorize reruns, I should then execute:\n- duplicate repeats,\n- equivalent-SMILES variants,\n- isolated single-entry runs,\n- and independently reordered mixed batches,\nin parallel where possible, for only the audited panel.' additional_kwargs={'refusal': None} response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 487, 'prompt_tokens': 2461, 'total_tokens': 2948, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 0}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'gpt-5.4-2026-03-05', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-DPi2Bj02FP68u6xq5YtwAEWpmD0xO', 'service_tier': 'default', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None} id='lc_run--019d476d-50b7-7a82-8909-ea2b10eb9ef3-0' tool_calls=[] invalid_tool_calls=[] usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 2461, 'output_tokens': 487, 'total_tokens': 2948, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 0}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}}
